## ⚖️ Assumptions & Trade-offs

### 1. In-Memory Data Store
The backend uses an in-memory `Map` to store tickers and simulate price updates.

Trade-off:
- Simple and fast for demonstration
- Not persistent (resets on restart)
- No database integration

### 2. Simulated Market Data
Price updates are simulated at intervals rather than using real financial APIs.

Trade-off:
- Keeps the project self-contained
- Avoids dependency on third-party services

### 3. Single WebSocket Stream
All price updates are broadcasted without subscription-based filtering.

Trade-off:
- Simpler implementation
- In real-world systems, subscription-based streaming would improve scalability

### 4. No Authentication
The application assumes an open-access environment.

Trade-off:
- Simplifies architecture
- Not production-secure

